esearch and analyze cryptographic technologies and their use in various blockchain based systems advising CipherTrace\u2019s R&D staff on their security risks as well as the vulnerabilities of their implementation. Your work will have both theoretical and very practical components to it with a healthy mixture of computer science, math and software development. Requirements To be successful, you should have experience in the following areas: BS in Computer Science or Math or equivalent experience 2+years of experience in the blockchain ecosystem 5+years of experience as a Software Developer Deep understanding of zero knowledge proofs, bulletproofs, elliptic curve cryptography, and prominent signature schemes Knowledge of fault tolerant consensus protocols like PBFT and Raft Nice to have: MS in Computer Science,Cryptography or Understanding and hands-on experience in Bitcoin, Ethereum, and other blockchain technologies. Very familiar withLayer 1 and Layer 2 cryptographic protocols. Familiar with distributed systems and P2P networking protocols like Tor and I2P. Experience with offensive security and performing exploits. Experience with zk-STARK, Aurora, Bulletproofs, Halo, SNARK, and SONIC A love for all things crypto! Perks & Benefits We offer a comprehensive benefits package including competitive salaries, stock options for senior roles, medical, dental and vision \u2013 which cover domestic partners as well \u2013 plus life and disability coverage, 20 vacation days, and a 401K plan. ", 
